        "type": "website",
        "content": "type: search_result\ntitle: \"Your Annual Skin Health Checklist: What to Schedule and When\"\nurl: \"https://dermgroup.org/annual-skin-health-checklist/\"\ndescription: \"Scheduling early in the year often makes it easier to plan follow-up visits and stay consistent with care. New patients can review what to expect and prepare for their first visit here: New Patients. Your skin changes throughout your life, and proactive care is the best way to protect it. By scheduling key dermatology visits at the start of the year, you set yourself up for healthier skin and fewer surprises down the road. Ready to get started? Schedule an appointment ...\"\npage_age: \"February 11, 2026\"\nprofile_name: Dermatology Group of The Carolinas\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/kvPdx_nqj1ryEXM2zBT7fnjVS7RinwuQOQmK80bZNDY/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvMGFkNTNkZGE0/N2IyZGQzMjg4MDMy/NmY3M2ZmMDBmN2M2/Y2FiMmVjODY4ZDkz/YjAwNjczMDA2ZDZl/OWQ1YTI2OS9kZXJt/Z3JvdXAub3JnLw\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/q1_qOBTWkYufNqreGrt1VsrwHpAeP-AgD5hMTEAys7o/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9kZXJt/Z3JvdXAub3JnL3dw/LWNvbnRlbnQvdXBs/b2Fkcy8yMDI2LzAy/L0FubnVhbC1Ta2lu/LWhlYWx0aC1jaGVj/a2xpc3QtamFudWFy/eS0yMDI2LnBuZw\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://dermgroup.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Annual-Skin-health-checklist-january-2026.png\"\nextra_snippets: \"Scheduling early in the year often makes it easier to plan follow-up visits and stay consistent with care. New patients can review what to expect and prepare for their first visit here: New Patients. Your skin changes throughout your life, and proactive care is the best way to protect it. By scheduling key dermatology visits at the start of the year, you set yourself up for healthier skin and fewer surprises down the road. Ready to get started? Schedule an appointment with Dermgroup today and begin the year with a clear plan for your skin health.|The start of a new year is the perfect time to focus on preventive health—and your skin should be part of that plan. Your skin is your body’s largest organ, and regular dermatology visits can help detect issues early, manage chronic conditions, and keep your skin looking and feeling its best.|Regular follow-up appointments allow your Dermgroup physician to adjust medications, evaluate progress, and help prevent flare-ups before they become disruptive to daily life. Explore the full range of conditions we treat here: Conditions Treated. Your skin’s needs change throughout the year. Winter dryness, summer sun exposure, and environmental shifts can all affect skin health. Planning dermatology visits with the seasons in mind can help keep your skin balanced year-round.|This annual skin health checklist outlines which dermatology appointments and treatments to consider throughout the year so you can stay proactive instead of reactive when it comes to your skin.\"\nhash: b2d24a96b6fa6a1e\nembed_ref: dermgroup.org-NI8\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
