        "type": "website",
        "content": "type: search_result\ntitle: Preparing for a Dermatology Appointment | Cumberland Skin\nurl: \"https://www.cumberlandskin.com/healthy-skin-blog/your-essential-guide-to-preparing-for-a-dermatology-appointment\"\ndescription: \"Your dermatology provider will ... sure to share vital information on your skin history, surgery history, past treatments, current medications and supplements, and anything else that might impact the health of your skin...\"\npage_age: \"\"\nprofile_name: Cumberland Skin\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/9E98ofbfmhlGxOF4tOcHeEeblcDePpzrBsKkpBGX8w8/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvNzYxM2U5Yzg4/YTQ5MWIyMDFjYzUx/MzE5Yjg4NWI3ZWI3/MGJjZWZlNjllZTU5/YTBlMjMxYmZjN2Nj/YmEyMjIyYS93d3cu/Y3VtYmVybGFuZHNr/aW4uY29tLw\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/xd0YmcJs2yKG6fRPmIhC0blSzQDY_R4PJuUNJUAH8QY/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu/Y3VtYmVybGFuZHNr/aW4uY29tOjQ0My9n/ZXRtZWRpYS83YjY4/NjdhNy1jNDIyLTRi/YTAtOTA1YS0xZDMx/NmI0ODAzNDUvSG93/LUdldC1EZXJtLUFw/cHQtSGVyby1TLmpw/Zz93aWR0aD03MjAm/YW1wO2hlaWdodD00/MDAmYW1wO2V4dD0u/anBn\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://www.cumberlandskin.com:443/getmedia/7b6867a7-c422-4ba0-905a-1d316b480345/How-Get-Derm-Appt-Hero-S.jpg?width=720&amp;height=400&amp;ext=.jpg\"\nextra_snippets: \"Get prepared for your dermatology appointment with tips on what to expect and how to make the most of your visit at Cumberland Skin Surgery and Dermatology.|This visual aid is especially valuable if your skin is clear at the time of your appointment but gets worse on a regular basis. Furthermore, if you have regular flare-ups but aren’t sure what the condition is, your doctor can help identify the skin condition through photos. Do you have lots of questions about your skin, hair, and nails? Create a list of questions you’d like to ask your dermatologist in the weeks and days leading up to your appointment.|Instead, we recommend coming to your dermatology appointment barefaced or with minimal makeup so your doctor can get an optimal idea of the health of your skin. In preparation for your dermatology appointment, remove all nail polish from your fingers and toes.|Your dermatology provider will be meeting you for the first time, so make sure to share vital information on your skin history, surgery history, past treatments, current medications and supplements, and anything else that might impact the health of your skin. We recommend putting together a helpful list you can refer to before your appointment so it’s all ready to go when you get there.\"\nhash: f1d8a7b5c3a781a1\nembed_ref: cumberlandskin.com-LpI\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
